    "text": "By Joe Marino, Katherine Donlevy ,\n2 hours ago\nA career criminal who was freed without bail on gun charges last summer was shot by police in the Bronx Friday, according to law enforcement sources.\nThe reputed member of the “Slutty Gang” was wounded at 755 White Plains Road in Clason Point shortly after 3 p.m. when cops responded to a dispute over a firearm, sources told The Post.\nTwo teens slashed at NYC subway platforms in separate attacks\nThe perpetrator, whose name has not been released, was struck in the left leg and taken to Jacobi Hospital, where his wounds were described as serious.\nOfficers were not injured in the shooting, though one was sent to the hospital with tinnitus.\nThe Bronx mansion of the late lyrical poet Stanley Moss sees a nearly $1M price cut mere months after his death\nThe suspect has four prior arrests, including one in August for toting a loaded revolver in Washington Heights.\nCLICK HERE TO SIGN UP FOR OUR METRO DAILY NEWSLETTER\nDespite his past, he was freed the following month without posting bail.\nThe perpetrator was also the victim in a January 2023 shooting, according to sources.\nThe investigation is ongoing.\nFor the latest metro stories, top headlines, breaking news and more, visit nypost.com/metro/",
